ia-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 30, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bwv1665702644903.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bwv1665702644903.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bwv1665702644903.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bwv1665702644903\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n umeter (Meter)\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__umetermeter__371803\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">umeter</code> widget displays the value of a Numeric field on a gauge for which there is a predefined range of values marked around the outer edge. Uniface provides a logical widget called Meter, which is mapped to <code class=\"ph codeph\">umeter</code>.\n </p>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__fig_w949ab1b5b3b1_w950ab1b5b3_w951ab1b5_w952ab1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Meter Widget </figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Meter widget with colored rim\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/meter_colors.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div><p class=\"p\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"akm1704707836734.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/akm1704707836734.html\" title=\"By default, Uniface displays most fields as edit boxes, but you can change this by selecting a different widget and optionally setting its widget properties. You can do this at the model level, for example in modeled entities or modeled components, or you can do this in the components themselves.\">Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13472e1_d13473e1_d13474e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Widget Overview</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Logical widget name:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Meter\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Maps to physical widget:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">umeter \n \n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Default definition:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Meter=umeter</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Use for:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n String fields with ValRep list.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Supported triggers:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bqj1665702585000.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bqj1665702585000.html\" title=\"Trigger that responds to an interactive event on a field or entity widget, such as the user clicking on the field.\">trigger detail</a>—activated when the user double-clicks the meter widget\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Supported properties:\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">See <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#bwv1665702644903__topic_d80162e1_d80163e1_d80164e1_d80165e1_d80166e1\">Widget Properties</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Supported in <p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">egrid</code>\n</p>(Grid) widget?\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n No\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n Supports MSAA? :\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n No\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__topic_d80152e1_d80153e1_d80154e1_d80155e1_d80156e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d607282e199\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__p_d113159e1_d113160e1_d113161e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">umeter</code> widget is a graphical representation of numeric data. The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Sweep Angle</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Start Angle</span> properties define the exact view of the widget. The widget is read-only; the user cannot edit its value.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__p_d113162e1_d113163e1_d113164e1\">This widget is not available in character mode. It is mapped to an edit box.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__topic_d80157e1_d80158e1_d80159e1_d80160e1_d80161e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d607282e220\">\n                       \n ValRep Handling\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__p_d113168e1_d113169e1_d113170e1\">The ValRep for this widget consists of a range of values, with optional rim color. It is possible to specify multiple ranges, each with their associated Uniface index color.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__p_d113171e1_d113172e1_d113173e1\">For example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">$valrep(METER)=\"1:25=16<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>25:75=48<span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>75:100=32\"</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__p_d113174e1_d113175e1_d113176e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cen1665702644981.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cen1665702644981.html\" title=\"Range of values displayed by the widget, with optional rim color. Multiple sub-ranges can also be specified. By default, the range is 0:100.\">Range and Color</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fya1665702645056.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fya1665702645056.html\" title=\"Uniface index colors are combinations of foreground an background colors that are identified by a color code, a number from 0 to 63.\">Uniface Index Colors</a> .</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__topic_d80162e1_d80163e1_d80164e1_d80165e1_d80166e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d607282e262\">\n                       \n                       Widget Properties\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Meter Widget Properties</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Property</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Technical name</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Dynamic?</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"txj1665702628158.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/txj1665702628158.html\" title=\"This property determines whether a three-dimensional appearance is applied when the widget is displayed. True (default) or False.\">3-D Effect (3d)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">3D</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bou1665702610816.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bou1665702610816.html\" title=\"The Attach to Window Border (Attach) widget property attaches the widget (or area frame) to one or more form window borders or split bars at runtime. This allows the element to be resized or moved when the window is resized or a split bar moved.\">Attach to Window Border (attach)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Attach</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rwc1665702587483.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rwc1665702587483.html\" title=\"Color to use as the background of the object.\">Background Color (BackColor)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">BackColor</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rbp1665702587714.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rbp1665702587714.html\" title=\"Color to use as the foreground (usually the text color).\">Foreground Color (ForeColor)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">ForeColor</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"svg1665702629592.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/svg1665702629592.html\" title=\"Determines whether a border is displayed around the widget at run time. True or False. The default value depends on the widget.\">Frame</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Frame</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mdg1665702628370.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mdg1665702628370.html\" title=\"Font for the label associated with this widget. The specified label font is also used in widgets that support tool tip text. If not specified, the font definition in the application's .ini file is used.\">Label Font ( LabelFont)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">LabelFont</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ryw1665702646481.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ryw1665702646481.html\" title=\"Number of annotated units displayed on the meter or slider widget. The default value is 4.\">Major Tick Units ( MajorTickUnits)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">MajorTickUnits</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tzo1665702646556.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tzo1665702646556.html\" title=\"Number of units that are displayed between two major ticks. The default is 5.\">Minor Tick Units ( MinorTickUnits)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">MinorTickUnits</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cen1665702644981.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cen1665702644981.html\" title=\"Range of values displayed by the widget, with optional rim color. Multiple sub-ranges can also be specified. By default, the range is 0:100.\">Range and Color</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wwg1665702587409.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wwg1665702587409.html\" title=\"Code that identifies a Uniface index color, which represents a combination of background and foreground colors. Applicable only to Form components. Deprecated.\">Index Color</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Range</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Color</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xrv1665702646629.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrv1665702646629.html\" title=\"Thickness of the meter scale relative to the widget as a whole. Allowed values are integers or floating point numbers. Default is 5 percent or 2 pixels, whichever is greater.\">Rim Thickness (Rim)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Rim</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wxw1665702646699.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wxw1665702646699.html\" title=\"Point on a circle where the meter scale begins, expressed in degrees. Values can be positive integer or floating point numbers. The default is 270 (degrees).\">Starting Angle ( StartAngle)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">StartAngle</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yxv1665702646775.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yxv1665702646775.html\" title=\"Positive or negative distance that the meter scale travels from its starting point, expressed in degrees. Values can be integer or floating point numbers. A negative value indicates reverse sweeping. Default is 180.\">Sweep Angle ( SweepAngle)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">SweepAngle</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"myn1665702646849.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/myn1665702646849.html\" title=\"Determines whether labels (annotations) are displayed for each major tick. True (default) or False.\">Visible Annotation ( Annotation)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Annotation</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kfj1665702629663.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kfj1665702629663.html\" title=\"The Widget Font ( Font) property determines the font used to display the text in this widget.\">Widget Font ( Font)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Font</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qff1665702581606.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qff1665702581606.html\" title=\"Defines the position and size of a rectangle to use as an anchor for a popup form, in character cells or pixels. The default value is 0,0,0,0.\">Popup Rectangle (PopupRect)</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">PopupRect</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"bwv1665702644903__table_d13475e1_d13476e1_d13477e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hdy1665702557196.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ValRep</a><p>This property defines the possible values that the field accepts. The ValRep consists of a Uniface list of one or more items, in which each item consists of a value and optional representation.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526277\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526277\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "umeter (Meter) Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 30, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 umeter (Meter) The umeter widget displays the value of a Numeric field on a gauge for which there is a predefined range of values marked around the outer edge. Uniface provides a logical widget called Meter, which is mapped to umeter . Figure 1. Meter Widget For more information, see Specifying a Widget for a Field or Entity . Table 1. Widget Overview Logical widget name: Meter Maps to physical widget: umeter Default definition: Meter=umeter Use for: String fields with ValRep list. Supported triggers: trigger detail —activated when the user double-clicks the meter widget Supported properties: See Widget Properties Supported in egrid (Grid) widget? No Supports MSAA? : No Description The umeter widget is a graphical representation of numeric data. The Sweep Angle and Start Angle properties define the exact view of the widget. The widget is read-only; the user cannot edit its value. This widget is not available in character mode. It is mapped to an edit box. ValRep Handling The ValRep for this widget consists of a range of values, with optional rim color. It is possible to specify multiple ranges, each with their associated Uniface index color. For example: $valrep(METER)=\"1:25=16 ; 25:75=48 ; 75:100=32\" For more information, see Range and Color and Uniface Index Colors . Widget Properties Table 2. Meter Widget Properties Property Technical name Dynamic? 3-D Effect (3d) 3D Yes Attach to Window Border (attach) Attach Yes Background Color (BackColor) BackColor Yes Foreground Color (ForeColor) ForeColor Yes Frame Frame Yes Label Font ( LabelFont) LabelFont Yes Major Tick Units ( MajorTickUnits) MajorTickUnits Yes Minor Tick Units ( MinorTickUnits) MinorTickUnits Yes Range and Color and Index Color Range Color Yes Rim Thickness (Rim) Rim Yes Starting Angle ( StartAngle) StartAngle Yes Sweep Angle ( SweepAngle) SweepAngle Yes Visible Annotation ( Annotation) Annotation Yes Widget Font ( Font) Font Yes Popup Rectangle (PopupRect) PopupRect Yes Related Links ValRep This property defines the possible values that the field accepts. The ValRep consists of a Uniface list of one or more items, in which each item consists of a value and optional representation. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}